postSelections

public void postSelections()
Post the lov selection into the categories after the user has pressed done in LOV. This will take the selections made in #setCategorySelection and push them into categories, as well as remove any subtree of FilterItems. This will be added back after the search is performed when this metadata is available.

Overrides:
postSelections in class SearchFilterItem

getInlineSelectionType

public java.lang.String getInlineSelectionType()
Description copied from class: SearchFilterItem
If isInlineSelection() == true, what type of selection is required?

Current types are "multiple" and "single" for selecting String types. By default, we are selection type single.

Specified by:
getInlineSelectionType in interface TilePart
Overrides:
getInlineSelectionType in class SearchFilterItem
Returns:
